iForeword: "Here we solemnly pledge: nothing shall separate me from the		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
idestiny of my motherland—neither natural disasters nor human		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
icalamities; neither wealth nor power; neither illness nor toil. This		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
iis our resolve. Henceforth, I shall strive diligently, seek knowledge		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
iabove and below, think deeply, and act courageously. This is our		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
ipractice. Until the nation is rejuvenated and the world embraces great		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
iharmony, this heart shall not rest. This is our public duty. With a		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
ipure heart, witnessed by mountains and rivers. Engraved in gold and		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
istone as mutual encouragement." — This is an oath inscribed at the		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
iZhijiang Campus of Hangzhou No.2 High School. From the merger of		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
imissionary W.M. Hayes' Huilan Middle School and the Zhejiang		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
iUniversity Affiliated High School founded by Mr. Zhu Kezhen, to		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
itoday's Hangzhou No.2 High School Education Group—a rare public school		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
isystem with five subordinate schools—it has traversed a legendary		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
ijourney. Today, let us step into this enigmatic provincial leading		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
ischool through a series of anniversary features!		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
