i- One day, it was my turn to change the water jug. For convenience, I		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
irolled it on the ground. Suddenly, someone called from behind:		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
i"Student ahead, stop! Seems the freshmen's arm strength isn't up to		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
ipar! Carry the water on your shoulder! We		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
iE Zhong		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
ipeople must have the responsibility to shoulder difficulties! We must		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
itoughen our bodies! We must— Eh? You're already at my principal's		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
ioffice? Where's your classroom?" I replied sheepishly: "On the 2nd		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
ifloor... but you kept talking, so I followed you to the 4th."		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
