ifor a complete collection of HZ2 teacher quotes. As the sole male		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
irepresentative from our year's liberal arts class, tasked with this, I		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
ifelt both trepidation and duty. Thanks to alumni for providing		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
imaterial and teachers for their permission, easing worries about		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
iaffecting their image. My collection is limited; many classics from		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
iless familiar teachers are surely missing due to my oversight. Fellow		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
ialumni, please enlighten me. I propose:		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
iStep 1: Every HZ2 alum or friend who reads this, please share it so		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
imore can see our alma mater's classics.
